#: ../../../reference/random/bit_generators/sfc64.rst:2
msgid "SFC64 Small Fast Chaotic PRNG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:2
msgid "BitGenerator for Chris Doty-Humphrey's Small Fast Chaotic PRNG."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:22
msgid "**seed**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:-1
msgid "{None, int, array_like[ints], SeedSequence}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:8
msgid ""
"A seed to initialize the `BitGenerator`. If None, then fresh, unpredictable "
"entropy will be pulled from the OS. If an ``int`` or ``array_like[ints]`` is "
"passed, then it will be passed to `SeedSequence` to derive the initial "
"`BitGenerator` state. One may also pass in a `SeedSequence` instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:25
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:26
msgid ""
"`SFC64` is a 256-bit implementation of Chris Doty-Humphrey's Small Fast "
"Chaotic PRNG ([R50352647a6aa-1]_). `SFC64` has a few different cycles that "
"one might be on, depending on the seed; the expected period will be about :"
"math:`2^{255}` ([R50352647a6aa-2]_). `SFC64` incorporates a 64-bit counter "
"which means that the absolute minimum cycle length is :math:`2^{64}` and "
"that distinct seeds will not run into each other for at least :math:`2^{64}` "
"iterations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:33
msgid ""
"`SFC64` provides a capsule containing function pointers that produce "
"doubles, and unsigned 32 and 64- bit integers. These are not directly "
"consumable in Python and must be consumed by a `Generator` or similar object "
"that supports low-level access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:38
msgid "**State and Seeding**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:40
msgid ""
"The `SFC64` state vector consists of 4 unsigned 64-bit values. The last is a "
"64-bit counter that increments by 1 each iteration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:43
msgid ""
"The input seed is processed by `SeedSequence` to generate the first 3 "
"values, then the `SFC64` algorithm is iterated a small number of times to "
"mix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:47
msgid "**Compatibility Guarantee**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._sfc64.SFC64:49
msgid ""
"`SFC64` makes a guarantee that a fixed seed will always produce the same "
"random integer stream."
msgstr ""

